This selection mechanism resonates with the concept of topological protection in condensed matter systems. In fractional quantum Hall states, quasiparticle excitations are topologically protected against local perturbations, ensuring their stability [13]. Similarly, the "hard core + soft shell" architecture provides topological protection against collisional disruption.

